      <section eId="sec_399_R">
        <num>399-R</num>
        <heading>Sale of paint pellet guns</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_R__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>No person, firm, or\ncorporation shall sell or offer to sell a paint pellet gun to any person\nunder sixteen years of age.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_R__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>For purposes of this subdivision, the term "paint pellet gun"\nmeans a gun, air gun, pistol, rifle, or like device in appearance or\nfunction, capable of and designed for discharging and propelling through\nthe air to a target a small quantity of paint enclosed within a pellet\nor pellet-like device or capsule or capsule-like device that breaks upon\nimpact with the target, overspreading the target with paint.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_399_R__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Any person, firm, or corporation who violates the provisions of\nthis section shall be subject to a civil penalty of not more than five\nhundred dollars.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
